A man has been arrested following the seizure of â‚¬30,000 worth of suspected cannabis in Galway. The drugs were discovered during a warrant search of a property in the Knocknacarra area on Tuesday. It was carried out as part of Operation Tara, targeting drug distribution. A man aged in his 50s was arrested at the scene and detained under Section 4 of the Criminal Justice Act at North Western Regional Headquarters in Galway. He was released without charge and a file is being prepared for the Director of Public Prosecutions.